	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101655136170360><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101655136170360>RE: Mana</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101655136170360#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=149180><span id= >satanbob</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 19th 10:25 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards are indeed Int casters. The bard mana pool is not affected by items that give additional mana. However, our mana pool is affected by Int raising spells and items.<br><br>Example: Diamond Wedding Band AC2 Dex3 Int5 Mana15. The bard mana pool is not increased by the 15 mana, but is increased by the 5 int.<br><br>Lastly, Bards are not affected by mana song, replenishment song, or any form of clarity. In addition, we are stuck with meditate at 1.<br><br>Outie. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
