	   <a name=101542836460001></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101542836460001><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101542836460001>RE: twisting songs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101542836460001#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1200><span id=Scholar>Lord Thayn</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>221 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 6th 10:27 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The most effective way I personally hae found to twist songs is to L-Click each Icon until it comes free and place it in the Hotkey box. This way I can activate each song by pressing a number instead of trying to move the mouse around.<br>&lt;Example&gt;<br>Enter combat and hit #1 (Chant of Battle)<br>Wait till you get the message You feel your pulse quicken.<br>Hit #1 again, or #2 (To cancel the first song) then #2 again (To begin singing the song in slot 2).<br><br>Rinse and repeat... this is much easier than mouse clicking because in some high-end and fast paced encounters, you can sometimes &quot;lose&quot; your cursor on the screen, and often you need to be doing other things with the cursor... but the number keys on your keyboard are there. I have even found the fingers still remember after having not played bard for several months.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Zaloren V'Shnev<br>Enchanter of Innoruuk<br>Master Jeweler<br>Journeyman Smith<br>Vazaelle</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
