	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 1st 1:46 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Head to MM and get your drums and grab the Lute of Gypsy Princess while you're at.&nbsp;&nbsp;Head over to Steamfont and grab a Minotaur Horn for your wind slot and just stick with the Combine Horn for now.  You don't get your first useful brass song 'til your mid-20s (26 I think, Appalling Screech).  The reason I've listed the above instruments is that they're easy to obtain at your level and, though they lack stats, they all offer bonuses to the effectiveness of the song played.  As far as gear goes, keep the AC high and the resists up.  SS is wonderful for AC but lacks in saves.  I'd go for some resistance jewelry if you're taking the SS route.  Hope this helps a bit.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
