<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=101459900954230></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101459900954230><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101459900954230>RE: Autoattack problems?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101459900954230#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6400><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>100 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 24th 8:04 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is a common bug in high level groups. What it is is that there is a haste cap, or a limit to how high your haste can be. I am pretty sure the limit is somewhere around 80-150%, but not completely sure. So, with these high level bard songs that can exceed the haste cap, there comes a point to which you go like 20% over, then your autoattack is still on, but you are slowed down to maximum slow cap. So if you do experience these bugs, just stop using those songs, and the effect will go off, and you will attack again. Verant should fix this in the near future.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
