	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok lineender, here is the situation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a Bard I can tell you Soloing, Kiting, and DD on a Caster with Nukes is a problem, PvP or not.  Here's an advisable selection of songs to have up to Lvl. 29:<br><br>1.  Selo's Consonant Chain  <br>2.  Crission's Pixie Strike<br>3.  Chords of Dissonance<br>4.  Dennon's Disruptive Discord<br>5.  Brusco's Boastful Bellow<br>6.  Largo's Melodic Binding<br>7.  Selo's Accelerando<br>8.  Hymn of Restoration<br><br><br>Now, here is an ideal scenario (I'll use the Number of the song in the scenario.)<br><br>Root him with #1<br>Mez with #2 If it takes.  (Will interrupt casting)<br>DoT  With #3 and #4<br>Direct Damage with #5  (Interrupt casting again.)<br><br><br>Interrupt casting with either #2 or #3  at any time you need to.  Remeber if mezzed, use #3 for Direct Damage as not to break Mez.<br><br>Heal with #8<br><br>Use #7 if you neeed to run (NOTHING in the game will catch you if you have Nostrolo's Tambourine or better percussion instruments!)  <br><br>With mele thrown in, this should produce a successful outcome a greater percentage of the time.  Hope this helps some.  <br><br>Oh BTW, as a Bard, I don't think that one class is superior to another.  I honestly believe that it is ultimately the skills of the Man or Woman manning the keybord that dictates the outcome in battle.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
